gov.usgs.anss.cd11send

Class ZeroFilledSpan

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.cd11send.ZeroFilledSpan

  • public class ZeroFilledSpan
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represent a time series chunk which is zero filled if data is missing. The idea is to allow creation, population by a series of blocks which may not be contiguous or even in order. Constructors needs to deal with different data types and construction methods. Initially, this class assumed it would be created from a list of mini-seed blocks. However, it is quite likely it will need to be extended to allow a pre-allocation followed by many calls adding data to the timeseries.
